## 🔄 How It Works

### Message Flow: User Input → AI Response

```
1. User sends message (WhatsApp/SMS/Email/Web)
   │
   ▼
2. API Gateway (Express.js)
   ├─ JWT authentication
   ├─ Rate limiting
   ├─ CORS validation
   └─ Request logging
   │
   ▼
3. Semantic Router (LlamaIndex)
   - Embed message (text-embedding-3-small)
   - Cosine similarity vs agent profiles
   - Route to best-matching agent
   │
   ▼
4. Orchestrator (AutoGen Pattern)
   ├─ CEO receives founder messages
   ├─ GroupChat: CEO + PM plan together
   ├─ DAG planning for complex tasks
   └─ Compress history before handoff
   │
   ▼
5. Agent Hierarchy
   ├─ CEO (ceo.js) - Strategic planning
   │  ├─ Spawns specialist agents
   │  └─ Reflects on outcomes
   │
   ├─ PM (pm.js) - Task management
   │  ├─ Task Ledger (Magentic-One)
   │  ├─ Progress Ledger
   │  ├─ Quality checks (CrewAI pattern)
   │  └─ Replan on stall detection
   │
   ├─ Developer (developer.js) - Execution
   │  ├─ File operations (FileTool)
   │  ├─ Shell commands (ShellTool)
   │  ├─ Code execution (CodeTool)
   │  └─ Browser automation (BrowserTool)
   │
   ├─ QA (qa.js) - Validation
   │  ├─ Test discovery
   │  ├─ Execution
   │  └─ Bug reports
   │
   └─ Specialized (sales/support/content)
      └─ Business-specific workflows
   │
   ▼
6. Tool Execution (Strands Pattern)
   ├─ FileTool: Sandboxed read/write/patch
   ├─ ShellTool: Subprocess with timeouts
   ├─ CodeTool: Isolated Python REPL
   ├─ BrowserTool: HTTP fetch + HTML extraction
   └─ MCP Adapter: JSON-RPC 2.0 tool calls
   │
   ▼
7. Response
   ├─ CEO generates final report
   ├─ Stores in permanent memory (Google ADK)
   └─ Returns via original channel
```

### 3-Tier Memory Architecture (Google ADK)

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    TIER 1: TEMP                      │
│  (Per LLM turn, not persisted)                       │
│  - Current file context                              │
│  - Immediate tool outputs                            │
│  - Cleared each turn                                 │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                    │
                    ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   TIER 2: SESSION                    │
│  (Per task execution, persisted to DB)               │
│  - Files read in this task                           │
│  - Intermediate results                              │
│  - Cleared on task completion                        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                    │
                    ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                  TIER 3: PERMANENT                   │
│  (Forever, across all sessions)                      │
│  - Learned patterns                                  │
│  - Best practices                                    │
│  - Historical knowledge                              │
│  - Agents improve over time                          │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

